cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on Arabic word segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also compares two machine learning approaches, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions information retrieval, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of SVM and bi-LSTM RNN coupled with CRF suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
